        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"El_Muerte\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"8818\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n El_Muerte:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>cool does this version also work with a multi monitor setup?</p>\n<p>Feature request:<br>\n- ability to make panorama shots <img src=\"https://forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, I think. If you want I can test later night.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I know this is an old thread, but I think I have a valid question.<br>\nThe export to Maya, it comes up saying Export impossible, this is not a maya build.<br>\nAny chance of a workaround or an update?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Maybe not, Yaz0r release it without this option with his own in intentions I think. He already got some problems with other projects he have by making such export options.</p>",
